  <section class="hero contain-1440">
   <div class="hero-image" style="background: url('images/home-page/lanterns-1440x268.jpg') no-repeat center / cover">
    <div class="text">
     <h2>
      Asian Studies
     </h2>
    </div>
   </div>
  </section>
  <div id="page">
   <main class="content" id="main-content" tabindex="-1">
    <section class="contain-1120">
     <div class="section-top">
      <h3>
       Why Pursue Asian Studies?
      </h3>
      <div class="long-border-grey">
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="feature-one-item">
      <article class="feature-box">
       <div>
        <div class="swiper-wrapper">
         <div class="swiper-slide">
          <img alt="Indian manuscript image of Rama and Sita in the forest, c.1650 CE" src="images/home-page/indian-manuscript-artstor-630x355.jpg"/>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="feature-copy">
        <p>
         <span>
          Through the study of a relevant language -- Chinese, Hindi, Japanese, or Korean -- and coursework in history, the humanities, and the social sciences, you will gain a sophisticated critical understanding of a specific Asian region -- East, South, or Southeast -- or country. You will also learn to examine the world, and yourself, through the lens of another language and culture.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <a class="button" href="about/why-study-asian-studies.html">
          Learn More
         </a>
        </p>
       </div>
      </article>
     </div>
    </section>
    <section class="">
     <div class="home-news-events contain-1120">
      <section class="highlight">
       <h4>
        First-year Focus
       </h4>
       <div class="short-border-black">
       </div>
       <div class="description">
        <p>
         <span>
          The Asian Studies Program offers an interdisciplinary major that combines substantial training in a relevant language – Chinese, Hindi, Japanese, or Korean – and a stimulating, well-rounded mix of History, Humanities, and Social Science courses related to Asia.
         </span>
        </p>
       </div>
       <p class="button">
        <a href="undergraduate/first-year-focus.html">
         Read More
        </a>
       </p>
      </section>
      <section class="news-full">
       <h4>
        Recent News
       </h4>
       <div class="short-border-black">
       </div>
       <h5>
        <a href="www.humanities.northwestern.edu/people/fellows/fellows-2018-2019.html">
         Dr. Rajeev Kinra named Kaplan Fellow for 2018-2019
        </a>
       </h5>
       <h5>
        <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/15/books/review/junichiro-tanizaki-in-black-and-white.html?smprod=nytcore-iphone&amp;smid=nytcore-iphone-share">
         Professor Phyllis Leon's translation of Junichiro Tanizaki's "In Black and White" was reviewed in the New York Times
        </a>
       </h5>
       <h5>
        <a href="https://www.bloomsbury.com/us/post-fascist-japan-9781350025813/">
         Professor Laura Hein publishes new book on Post-Fascist Japan
        </a>
       </h5>
       <h5>
        <a href="http://www.acls.org/research/fellow.aspx?cid=85861805-590a-e711-9452-000c29879dd6">
         Asian Studies faculty member receives Henry Luce Foundation fellowship
        </a>
       </h5>
      </section>
     </div>
    </section>
